\v 31 and Darius the Mede received the kingdom at the age of sixty-two.
\c 6
\s1 The Plot against Daniel
\m 
\v 1 Now it pleased \w Darius|strong="H1868"\w* \w to|strong="H1868"\w* appoint 120 satraps \w to|strong="H1868"\w* rule throughout \w the|strong="H1868"\w* \w kingdom|strong="H4437"\w*,
\v 2 \w and|strong="H4437"\w* \w over|strong="H5922"\w* \w them|strong="H5922"\w* three administrators, including Daniel, \w to|strong="H5922"\w* \w whom|strong="H1768"\w* these satraps \w were|strong="H1934"\w* accountable \w so|strong="H1768"\w* \w that|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H3606"\w* king \w would|strong="H1934"\w* not suffer loss.
\v 3 \w Soon|strong="H4481"\w*, \w by|strong="H2941"\w* \w his|strong="H4481"\w* extraordinary spirit, \w Daniel|strong="H1841"\w* distinguished himself \w among|strong="H4481"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* administrators \w and|strong="H4430"\w* satraps. \w So|strong="H1768"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* \w king|strong="H4430"\w* planned \w to|strong="H4430"\w* set \w him|strong="H4481"\w* \w over|strong="H5924"\w* \w the|strong="H4481"\w* whole kingdom.
